      "side": 1,
      "message": "This complexity is needed to handle following cases:\n\nImagine in Starlark I have meta.config(fail_on_warnings \u003d True), but I want to temporary override this via command line flag to be False: `lucicfg validate ... -fail-on-warnings\u003dfalse`. But false is default value of this command line flag. So I need to know that a flag was explicitly passed.\n\nAlso I didn\u0027t want to have a ton of \u0027switch\u0027 statements that duplicate field names everywhere. Instead there\u0027s one filedsMap() and a sprinkle of reflection.",
